    • Method Detail

      • doInBackground

        protected org.json.JSONObject doInBackground(Stop... stops)
        Override this method to perform a computation on a background thread. The specified parameters are the parameters passed to execute(Params...) by the caller of this task. This will normally run on a background thread. But to better support testing frameworks, it is recommended that this also tolerates direct execution on the foreground thread, as part of the execute(Params...) call. This method can call publishProgress(Progress...) to publish updates on the UI thread. This method may take several seconds to complete, so it should only be called from a worker thread.
        Specified by:
        doInBackground in class android.os.AsyncTask<Stop,java.lang.Void,org.json.JSONObject>
        Parameters:
        stops - The parameters of the task. This should only be the stop that needs to retrieved by the RouteMatch object from the RouteMatch server.
        Returns:
        A result, defined by the subclass of this task. This should be the corresponding JSON from the RouteMatch server.

      • onPostExecute

        protected void onPostExecute(org.json.JSONObject result)
        Runs on the UI thread after doInBackground(Params...). The specified result is the value returned by doInBackground(Params...). To better support testing frameworks, it is recommended that this be written to tolerate direct execution as part of the execute() call. This current implementation will update the snippet of the stop's marker.

        This method won't be invoked if the task was cancelled.

        This method must be called from the Looper#getMainLooper() of your app.

        Overrides:
        onPostExecute in class android.os.AsyncTask<Stop,java.lang.Void,org.json.JSONObject>
        Parameters:
        result - The result of the operation computed by doInBackground(Params...).
